definition.value: A spermidine hydroxycinnamic acid conjugate in which each nitrogen of spermidine has entered into amide bond formation with a molecule of 4-coumaric acid.
An N-acetyl-L-amino acid, where the amino acid is L-2-aminoadipic acid (6-oxo-L-norleucine).

A spermidine hydroxycinnamic acid conjugate in which N-1 and N-5 of spermidine have formed amide bonds with a molecule each of 5-hydroxyferulic acid and N-10 has formed an amide bond with sinapic acid.
An acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 4-trimethylammoniobutanoic acid.
An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of D-psicose 6-phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.
A lipid A oxoanion obtained via deprotonation of the carboxy and phosphate OH groups of (KDO)2-(palmitoleoyl)-lipid IVA; major species at pH 7.3.
An L-glutamine derivative that is L-glutamine in which a hydrogen attached to the amide nitrogen is replaced by a 4-oxobutyl group.
A lipid A oxoanion obtained via deprotonation of the carboxy and phosphate OH groups of (KDO)2-(palmitoleoyl-myristoyl)-lipid A; major species at pH 7.3.
A lipid A derivative having an  L-alpha-D-Hep-(1->3)-L-alpha-D-Hep-(1->5)-[alpha-Kdo-(2->4)]-alpha-Kdo attached to the free primary hydroxy group of lipid A.
A lipid A oxoanion obtained via deprotonation of the carboxy and phosphate OH groups of (KDO)2-(lauroyl)-lipid IVA; major species at pH 7.3.
A hexadecenoyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (E)-hexadec-2-enoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of D-fructofuranose 6-phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.
A lipid A derivative having an L-alpha-D-Hep-(1->5)-[alpha-Kdo-(2->4)]-alpha-Kdo moiety attached to the free primary hydroxy group of lipid A.
A glycosylgalactose consisting of beta-D-galactose having an alpha-L-fucosyl residue attached at the 2-position.
An ADP-L-glycero-D-manno-heptose having beta-configuration at the anomeric centre of the heptose.
A butan-4-olide having a 2-chloroethyl group at the 3-position and two methyl substituents at the 5-position.
A poly(phenylene oxide) polymer, composed of poly(2,6-dimethyl-1,4-phenylene oxide) macromolecules.

A polyprenyl phospho oligosaccharide where alpha-D-FucNAc4-(1->4)-beta-D-ManNAcA-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc comprises the oligosaccharide component and is linked via a diphosphate to a polyprenyl chain consisting of eleven prenyl units.
A poly(phenylene oxide) polymer, composed of poly(1,4-phenylene oxide) macromolecules.
A poly(alkylene oxide) polymer, composed of poly(oxymethylene) macrmolecules.
A UDP-amino sugar having 3-O-[(3R)-3-hydroxytetradecanoyl]-N-acetyl-alpha-glucosamine as the amino sugar component.
A poly(oxymethylene) polymer, composed of paraformaldehyde macromolecules.
A butan-4-olide having a 2-bromoethyl group at the 3-position and two methyl substituents at the 5-position.
A hexadecenoyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of palmitoleyl-CoA.
A butan-4-olide having a 1-[(methylsulfonyl)oxy]ethyl group at the 3-position and two methyl substituents at the 5-position.
A butan-4-olide having a 3-bromopropyl group at the 3-position and two methyl substituents at the 5-position.
An undecaprenyldiphospho-N-acetylmuramoyl peptide in which the peptide element is L-alanyl-D-gamma-glutamyl-meso-2,6-diaminopimeloyl-D-alanyl-D-alanine.
A butan-4-olide having a 2-(tosyloxy)ethyl group at the 3-position and two methyl substituents at the 5-position.
A butan-4-olide having a 2-[(4-methoxyphenylsulfonyl)oxy]ethyl group at the 3-position and two methyl substituents at the 5-position.
A butan-4-olide having a 2-(phenylsulfonyloxy)ethyl group at the 3-position and two methyl substituents at the 5-position.
A butan-4-olide having a [1-(4-chlorophenylsulfonyl)oxy]ethyl group at the 3-position and two methyl substituents at the 5-position.
An organophosphate oxoanion resulting from deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of D-glucopyranose 6-phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.
A butan-4-olide having a [1-(4-nitrophenylsulfonyl)oxy]ethyl group at the 3-position and two methyl substituents at the 5-position.
A butan-4-olide having a 1-thiocyanatoethyl group at the 3-position and two methyl substituents at the 5-position.
A dihydrocarvone compound having the exocyclic isopropenyl double bond reduced and (R)-configuration.
A carvone compound comprising (R)-carvone having a 3-methyl substituent.
The five-membered ring form of D-fructose 6-phosphate.
A 2'-deoxyribonucleoside 5'-triphosphate(4-) resulting from deprotonation of the triphosphate OH groups of 2'-deoxyuridine-5'-triphosphate (dUTP); major species at pH 7.3.
A lipid A derivative, comprising lipid A glycosylated with two 3-deoxy-D-manno-octulosonic acid (KDO) residues and having the dodecanoyl group replaced by palmitoleoyl.
A ribonucleoside triphosphate oxoanion arising from global deprotonation of the  triphosphate groups of any nucleoside triphosphate; major species at pH 7.3.
A lipid A comprising lipid IVA glycosylated with two 3-deoxy-D-manno-octulosonic acid (KDO) residues and carrying an additional palmitoleoyl group.
A ketohexose monophosphate consisting of D-psicose having a phosphate group located at the 6-position.
A member of the class of  benzyl chlorides that is toluene substituted on the alpha-carbon with chlorine.
A 2'-deoxyribonucleoside triphosphate oxoanion being the tetraanion formed by global deprotonation of the triphosphate group.

A polyprenyl phospho oligosaccharide where beta-D-ManNAcA-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc comprises the oligosaccharide component and is linked via a diphosphate to a polyprenyl chain consisting of eleven prenyl units.
The nucleotide-sugar oxoanion which is the dianion formed from dTDP-4-acetamido-4,6-dideoxy-D-galactose by deprotonation of the two phosphate OH groups.
The organophosphate oxoanion that is the tetra-anion arising from deprotonation of all four free triphosphate OH groups of farnesyl triphosphate.
A tripeptide comprising L-alanyl, gamma-D-glutamyl and meso-diaminopimelic acid residues in a linear sequence. It is a breakdown product of bacterial peptidoglycan and a NOD1 agonist.
A dipeptide consisting of L-glutamic acid having an L-alanyl attached to its alpha-amino group
A dipeptide consisting of D-glutamic acid having an L-alanyl attached to its alpha-amino group
